title: Hogarth (World of Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Hogarth (World of Art)
Thames and Hudson | 1981 | ISBN: 050020182X | English | 220 pages | PDF | 32 MB

It gives you enough of the biographical and historical arc to provide a context for his work, and admirably unfolds the art for the reader. Since Hogarth's work was often social commentary, this book gives you the background a modern reader needs to understand the visual allusions that are so plentiful. Faithful reprints of his art with good detail make your exploration easier
